
Kubernetes (K8s) is an open-source platform used to manage, deploy, and scale containerized applications automatically.

*Why Kubernetes is Used?
✅ Automatically deploy applications
✅ Scale apps when traffic increases
✅ Restart failed containers (self-healing)
✅ Load balancing between users
✅ Manage multiple containers easily.

→ Basic Concepts of Kubernetes
1. 🟢 Cluster
A group of machines (nodes)
One Master Node + multiple Worker Nodes

2. 📦 Pod
Smallest unit in Kubernetes
Contains 1 or more containers
👉 Example: A web app container

3. 🚀 Deployment
Manages pods
Ensures correct number of pods are running

4. 🌐 Service
Exposes your app to users
Acts like a network endpoint

5. ⚙️ Node
A machine (VM or physical)
Runs pods


How Kubernetes Works (Simple Flow)
You create a deployment (app)
Kubernetes creates pods
Pods run on nodes
Service exposes the app
Kubernetes keeps monitoring & fixing issues.
